        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=4931&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Idea+for+a+change%2E%2E%2E"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I heard a rumor not long ago that our darkness spells decreased attack speed by a little.</P><P>Now, obviously this is just some newbie BS story, but wouldn't it be an incredible help if it were true?</P><P>It makes "RP" sense, for starters. Necros have always been big on multi-function spells (DMF, Asystole), and a monster enshrouded in unnatural darkness certainly wouldn't be attacking at the same rate as he normally would.</P><P>The one small change could also solve three big necro issues without hurting other classes.</P><P>We'd be the masters of soloing again, since it'd allow us to solo in dungeons where we couldn't before.</P><P>The effect on the epic could be made to have a higher percentage of slow than the 59 darkness, which would actually make it <i>usefull</i>. *gasp!*</P><P>Each successive spell in the darkness line could be made to have a little higher percentage of slow than the last, so we'd no longer be casting our 29 darkness in preference to our 49 or 59 (much like Shamans would once cast thier lower level canno...)</P><P>Slow effect spells are hardly unique to any one class, so the change wouldn't be encroaching on anyone's territory, but even so the slow effect on our darkness could be made to be inferior to and overwritten by enchanter or shaman slow.</P><P>I think the following would be appropriate:</P><P>Clinging - 0%<BR>Engulfing - 8-11%<BR>Dooming - 15-20%<BR>Cascading - 25-30%<BR>Devouring - 35-37%<BR>Duck Stick - 45%</P><P>I'm going to send this in to the new flameplay and hope they like the idea. What does everyone here think?</P><P><img src="http://members.bellatlantic.net/vze24qqk/public_html/truemara.jpg" border=0><BR>We're being punished for our solo ability.</font></td>
      </tr>

